  "title": "Draftsperson",
  "description": "<p>· Drafting of engineering and shop drawing</p>\n<p>· Coordinate with Project Manager, Project Team, Design Team and related person.</p>\n<p>· Prepare and review rough sketch and review them allow with the Engineering team.</p>\n<p>· Responsible for attending the meeting with consultants, contractors as part of project.</p>\n<p>· Familiarity with 3D modeling tools is preferred.</p>\n<p>· Required to maintain all drawing files, update drawings as needed, and make corrections to drawings as directed by the Section Heads / Leads</p>\n<p>· Coordination of drawings with Clients / Main Contractors and updating of drawings base on Meetings and discussion and in compliance to Regulation Codes and Practices</p>\n<p>· Explain drawings to production or construction teams and provide adjustments as necessary</p>\n<p>· Clarify and solve problems raised by teams</p>\n<p>· Coordinate with team members and other discipline</p>\n<p>· Other ad hoc duties assigned</p>\n<p><strong>Job Requirement:</strong></p>\n<p>· Minimum 2 years’ experience as a Draftsperson in the Metal work structural.</p>\n<p>· Must have knowledge in Aluminium, Stainless steel, cladding system and metal work.</p>\n<p>· At least Diploma in Building/Civil Engineering or equivalent.</p>\n<p>· Strong communication skills with teams and subcontractors .</p>\n<p>· 5.5 Days work week (Alt Saturday)</p>",
